# TypeScript

- Strict mode is on (`tsconfig.base.json`). Do not weaken `strict`, `noUncheckedIndexedAccess`, or related flags.
- Prefer `unknown` over `any`. ESLint `@typescript-eslint/no-explicit-any` is a warning тАФ avoid introducing new `any`.
- Do not use `{}` as a type (banned by `@typescript-eslint/ban-types`). Use `object`, `Record<string, unknown>`, or a named interface.
- Export both runtime values and types when CJS interop requires it (see `@retain/database` `PrismaClient` pattern: `export const` + `export type` with the same name).
- Node ESM packages use `.js` extensions in relative imports (`from './foo.js'`).
- After changing public types in `packages/*`, rebuild or ensure dependents typecheck (`pnpm typecheck`).

```typescript
// тЭМ BAD тАФ value-only export used as a type under isolated/CJS interop
export { PrismaClient };
// consumer: type X = { db: PrismaClient } // TS2749

// тЬЕ GOOD
export const PrismaClient = PrismaClientConstructor;
export type PrismaClient = PrismaClientType;
```
